i in\nsilicon as very long-lived spin qubits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:00:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Oct 2014 10:31:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 14 Mar 2015 09:49:29 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 13 May 2015 10:28:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
{"id":"1409.8656","submitter":"Pierre Clare","authors":"Pierre Clare, Tyrone Crisp and Nigel Higson","title":"Adjoint functors between categories of Hilbert C*-modules","comments":"Final version, to appear in the Journal of the Institute of\n  Mathematics of Jussieu","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1017/S1474748016000074","report-no":"CPH-SYM-DNRF92","categories":"math.OA math.RT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let E be a (right) Hilbert C*-module over a C*-algebra A. If E is equipped\nwith a left action of a second C*-algebra B, then tensor product with E gives\nrise to a functor from the category of Hilbert B-modules to the category of\nHilbert A-modules. The purpose of this paper is to study adjunctions between\nfunctors of this sort. We shall introduce a new kind of adjunction relation,\ncalled a local adjunction, that is weaker than the standard concept from\ncategory theory. We shall give several examples, the most important of which is\nthe functor of parabolic induction in the tempered representation theory of\nreal reductive groups. Each local adjunction gives rise to an ordinary\nadjunction of functors between categories of Hilbert space representations. In\nthis way we shall show that the parabolic induction functor has a simultaneous\nleft and right adjoint, namely the parabolic restriction functor constructed in\na previous paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Sep 2014 19:03:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 27 Jun 2015 21:10:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 23 Feb 2016 14:32:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-06"}
